ectors but become very slow for tuples with more than 32 elements. 
(run using Julia 1.9.0-alpha1, windows 64)
```
julia> r16 = rand(16) ; r32 = rand(32); r33 = rand(33); r64 = rand(64);
julia> t16 = Tuple(r16); t32 = Tuple(r32); t33 = Tuple(r33); t64 = Tuple(r64);

julia> (@btime maximum($r16)), (@btime maximum($t16));
  21.242 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  12.412 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia> (@btime maximum($r32)), (@btime maximum($t32));
  29.447 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  20.762 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia> (@btime maximum($r33)), (@btime maximum($t33));
  30.291 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  755.238 ns (35 allocations: 816 bytes)

julia> (@btime maximum($r64)), (@btime maximum($t64));
  54.813 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  1.330 μs (66 allocations: 1.55 KiB)


julia> (@btime sum($r16)), (@btime sum($t16));
  13.600 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  5.900 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia> (@btime sum($r32)), (@btime sum($t32));
  13.714 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  7.000 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia> (@btime sum($r33)), (@btime sum($t33));
  14.314 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  738.583 ns (35 allocations: 816 bytes)

julia> (@btime sum($r64)), (@btime sum($t64));
  14.214 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
  1.360 μs (66 allocations: 1.55 KiB)
